@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Do_mi_no" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  The idea is to create 28 dominos, using the patterns of dots (or
numbers) shown on the game board. To play, click on any tile you want
and then click on a neighbouring tile, that second tile must be
immediately next, either horizontally or vertically, to the previously
clicked tile. If the tiles are next to each other, a domino will be
formed, 'joining' the two tiles together. If one (or both) of the tiles
was already part of a domino, that previous domino will be 'reset'.

  If a domino having the same pattern of dots (or numbers) was previously
created, it will flash and the new domino will be reset.

  Continue the game until all 28 dominos are created... then Do_mi_no
will display how many moves you have made to complete the game.

  You can start a new game by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button, or
restart the same game by clicking on the @{b}Replay@{ub} button.

  You can choose the type of dominoes you want to play with, by
clicking on the @{b}Dots/Numbers@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

